result.name: 梁記餃子麵坊

reviews.text:
Very limited shop size, but indescribably delicious food :) The enormous, juicy meat ball is wrapped by a layer not so thin as to be torn by the weight of the meat, yet not so thick as to spoil the texture of the dumpling either.
The smoothness of the vermicelli makes swallowing easy and comfortable :)

Specialized mostly in dumplings.  Quite good, available in different fillings.
Currently $38 for a bowl of 8 mixed fillings, all big size.  Add $4 for a cold soy milk.
Low price and very home made quality
Food are good though the attitude of the staff sometimes really piss you off.
Authentic Chinese Dimsum, Price is a bit above average
